"{\"uid\": \"newsaf.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-08-Chinese-weightlifter-Li-wins-2nd-consecutive-Olympic-gold-1vSIjyIXM1q-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  China's Li Fabin retained his Olympic title in the men's 61kg weightlifting division at the Paris Olympics on Wednesday.  Li, 31, set an Olympic record of 143kg in the snatch and lifted 167kg in the clean and jerk to go with a winning total of 310kg.  This is the first weightlifting event contested at Paris 2024. Theerapong Silachai of Thailand bagged the silver medal with 303kg, while Hampton Morris of the United States took the bronze with 298kg.  (Cover image via CFP)  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"